                                        <fixVersion>1.0.5</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13159328" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 29 Nov 2011 16:01:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was that we were writing a FOWARD_HEADER with an empty byte array in case there were no local nodes to forward to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13159334" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 29 Nov 2011 16:05:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13159366" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 29 Nov 2011 17:04:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(for those running into this, note that you&apos;ll have to update &lt;b&gt;all&lt;/b&gt; nodes before stopping seeing the exception showing up)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
